itemDescription: George Cross recipient in World War II

wikipedia_page.main: Major André Gilbert Kempster,  (26 October 1916 – 21 August 1943), born André Gilberto Coccioletti, was awarded the George Cross posthumously "...in recognition of most conspicuous gallantry in carrying out hazardous work in a very brave manner" for an act of self-sacrifice in Algeria during the Second World War.
